Ready to dress up and strike a pose? Lens-based artist Claire Arni brings a trunk full of props and costumes for you to mix, match, and transform into whoever you want to be. Gather your gang, pick a costume, and snap a photo to remember the day. If you’d like Claire to click your portrait, swing by between 11:00 am and 1:00 pm. Can’t make it at that time? Don’t worry—we’ve got you covered. No fuss, just fun — and a printed photograph to take home!

&nbsp;

Engagement with various art mediums can profoundly impact one's creative journey. Each medium offers unique possibilities - both personally and professionally - from letting one express themselves to shaping one's perception of the world. The conversation between author Vivek Shanbhag and literary critic S R Vijayshankar takes us through that journey of a writer and his writing; inviting us to take a look at the relationship between writing and art.

Taking inspiration from the folk perforamce art of Yakshagana, Vivek Shanbhag’s works encompass characteristics of painting, dance, music, rhythms and improvisation. The discussion explores how one’s milestones are shaped by their thoughts and different kinds of art forms. Join Vivek Shanbhag and S R Vijayshankar as they delve into how medium could impact one's artistic style, experimenting leading to creative growth, and the emotional resonance it brings about.

This talk is in collaboration with Ananya Dhrishya.

